### Send Metrics to New Relic with .env (Zsh/Node)

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/test/benchmark/Readme.md

Configures and runs benchmarks to send metrics to New Relic's OTLP endpoint. It involves creating a `.env` file with the `NEW_RELIC_LICENSE_KEY` and optionally `NEW_RELIC_METRICS_HOST`, then running the benchmark script using Node with the environment file.

```zsh
# Starting at node-newrelic (root directory)
cd bin
touch .env
# Fill out NEW_RELIC_LICENSE_KEY=YOUR_INGEST_LICENSE_KEY
# If you are sending metrics to production instead of staging (default), also include: NEW_RELIC_METRICS_HOST=otlp.nr-data.net
node --env-file .env ./run-bench.js
```

