### Node.js: New Relic Configuration for Request Naming Rules

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet highlights new configuration parameters in the New Relic Node.js agent for defining rules to name or ignore requests. It references the README for examples, particularly on how to prevent socket.io traffic from impacting average response time metrics.

```javascript
// Example configuration snippet (actual parameter names might vary):
exports.config = {
  // ... other config options
  rules: {
    ignore: [
      { name: 'Background/Task/LongRunning' },
      { request_uri: '/socket.io/*' }
    ],
    rename: [
      { find: 'GET /api/old/*', replace: 'GET /api/v2/*' }
    ]
  }
};
```

